## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

**10 tests. 0 real verifications. This is a textbook coverage-touching suite.**

Every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called — in near-declaration order — but almost nothing is asserted. The 3 tests that do assert use only `Assert.IsNotNull`, which passes for any non-null return (including wrong data). This explains the 95% coverage with production bugs: the coverage tool sees every line executed, but no test actually checks that the code does the right thing.

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| Critical | 7 |
| High     | 0 |
| Medium   | 2 |
| Low      | 1 |

---

### Critical Findings

#### 1. Coverage-touching pattern (systemic — all 10 tests)

The entire class is a coverage-inflation suite. Methods are called in declaration order with zero or trivial assertions. Seven tests have **no assertion at all** or only `Assert.IsNotNull`:

| Test method | Problem |
|---|---|
| `AddProduct_Works` (L17) | No assertion. Did the product actually get stored? |
| `GetProduct_Works` (L23) | `IsNotNull` — never checks SKU, name, or price match. |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` (L31) | No assertion. Price may not have changed. |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` (L39) | No assertion. Product may still exist. |
| `SearchProducts_Works` (L45) | `IsNotNull` — never checks count or content. Could return empty list and pass. |
| `GetAllProducts_Works` (L55) | `IsNotNull` — never checks the list has the added product. |
| `GetProductCount_Works` (L62) | No assertion at all. Result is discarded. |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (L68) | No assertion. Prices may be unchanged or wrong. |
| `ExportToCsv_Works` (L76) | `IsNotNull` — never checks CSV content. |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` (L84) | No assertion. Data may not have been imported. |

**Concrete fixes** (showing 3 representative examples):

```csharp
// AddProduct — BEFORE (L17-21)
public void AddProduct_Works()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);
}

// AddProduct — AFTER
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_StoresProductRetrievableBySku()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored?.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored?.Price);
}
```

```csharp
// UpdatePrice — BEFORE (L31-36)
